quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,130,""
  37,131,"Verily, thus do We reward the Muhsinûn (good-doers, who perform good deeds totally for Allâh’s sake only - See V.2:112)."
  37,132,"Verily, he was one of Our believing slaves."
  40,73,"Then it will be said to them: ",1:[{40:73} See the footnote of {4:135}.]
  40,74,"",1:[{40:74} See the footnote of {2:165}.]
  40,75,"That was because you had been exulting in the earth without any right (by worshipping others instead of Allâh and by committing crimes), and that you used to rejoice extremely (in your error)."
  41,52,"Say: "
  41,53,"We will show them Our Signs in the universe, and in their own selves, until it becomes manifest to them that this (the Qur’ân) is the truth. Is it not sufficient in regard to your Lord that He is a Witness over all things?"
  41,54,"Verily they are in doubt concerning the Meeting with their Lord? (i.e. Resurrection after their death, and their return to their Lord). Verily! He it is Who is surrounding all things!"
  42,37,"And those who avoid the greater sins,{1} and Al-Fawâhish (illegal sexual intercourse), and when they are angry, forgive.{2}",1:[ {42:37} e.g. to join partners in worship with Allah, to be undutiful to one’s parents, to commit murder, to give false statements and witnesses, to steal (See Verse {6:151} and {6:152}).],2:[{42:37}.]
a) See the footnote (B) of {3:130} and {3:134}.
b) See the footnote of {2:22}.
c) See the footnote of {4:135}.
d) See the footnote of {2:278}.
  42,38,"And those who answer the Call of their Lord [i.e. to believe that He is the only One Lord (Allâh), and to worship none but Him Alone], and perform As-Salât (Iqâmat-as-Salât), and who (conduct) their affairs by mutual consultation, and who spend of what We have bestowed on them."
  42,39,"And those who, when an oppressive wrong is done to them, take revenge."
  43,19,"And they make the angels who themselves are slaves of the Most Gracious (Allâh) females. Did they witness their creation? Their testimony will be recorded, and they will be questioned!"
  43,20,"And they said: "
  43,21,"Or have We given them any Book before this (the Qur’ân) to which they are holding fast?"
  44,4,"Therein (that night) is decreed every matter of ordainments.{1}",1:[{44:4} i.e. the matters of deaths, births, provisions, calamities, etc. for the whole (coming) year as decreed by Allah.]
  44,5,"As a Command (or this Qur’ân or the Decree of every matter) from Us. Verily, We are ever sending (the Messengers),"
  44,6,"(As) a Mercy from your Lord. Verily, He is the All-Hearer, the All-Knower."
